About us
Any company that wants to offer payment and banking services faces numerous regulatory and technological barriers. Through Hash, any B2B company can offer its customers business advantages by eliminating transaction friction and offering other benefits related to their core operation. Our white label and plug-and-play platform minimizes implementation time, reduces initial investment and operating costs by up to 95%.

On our daily basis, we understand the value of collaboration, and we strive for a healthy environment. Flexible work hours, pet friendly office, yoga and massage are cool, but they're simply a reflex of autonomy as a core value of our team.
How we work in our tech team
As part of our day-to-day work we have 5 pillars that serve as a mental framework that guides us on how to approach situations, make decisions and work better together:
HIGH-QUALITY CODEBASE
We are building the company and its applications for the long haul.
We are an infrastructure company that deals with money, which is a critical resource in people's lives. Our foundations have to be solid, so we can deliver value to our customers, not only today but also in the future. An unchecked mistake now can lead to unforeseen regret.
START-TO-FINISH OWNERSHIP
You are responsible not only for what you are doing but also for all areas that permeate the product that you are working on. This will bring you a wider vision of people that will be affected by your work.
You are not just developing software, you are part of a team-building a product. From the inception of the idea to daily maintenance and operation, it's YOUR product.
PRODUCT-DRIVEN
We are Product-driven. Your mindset should always be thinking about the perspective of the product and the business value we are delivering. Question everyone in the team to understand why and what are the priorities of what we are building.
SEEK HELP AND SUPPORT OTHERS
We are not alone in the company, and we don't know all the answers. It is important to be humble and understand that gathering ideas and information from others will lead us to a better resolution.
OPEN COMMUNICATION
Working with open and reliable people are one of our greatest values, and we need this to expand to all the areas we can. Open communication builds trust and without that, we wouldn't be where we are. Always try to be upfront with issues, problems, even if individual, the only bad news is no news.
