About us
Any company that wants to offer payment and banking services faces numerous regulatory and technological barriers. Through Hash, any B2B company can offer its customers business advantages by eliminating transaction friction and offering other benefits related to their core operation. Our white label and plug-and-play platform minimizes implementation time, reduces initial investment and operating costs by up to 95%.
On our daily basis, we understand the value of collaboration, and we strive for a healthy environment. Flexible work hours, pet friendly office, yoga and massage are cool, but they're simply a reflex of autonomy as a core value of our team.

About the role
Our business is extremely abstract, and its nature has a high level of complexity. That's why we seek designers who can abstract, understand, and develop solutions at all levels of the organization. We believe that the essence of the area is to solve problems and materialize the intangible with purpose. Our team requires a high level of technical execution, zeal for their deliverables, and above all, deconstruct beliefs. Always seeking a diversity of perspectives, our designers cannot have attachment and ego about their deliverables.
To build this infrastructure, we need to design an amazing and scalable product. "Go horse culture" doesn't really work for the type of systems that we build. We tend to reduce technical debt and prioritize quality over a fast release.
We are not attached to a specific set of tools or frameworks, we have several challenges, and you will be free to choose the best way to attack each one of them. Everyone in our team has the autonomy to develop the assigned projects directly with other roles.
What about research? Yes. We believe research is essential for a consistent high impact product, but we do not solely assign the designer roles in the upstream. We have a research area that, together with our team, capture, process, analyze, idealize, validate hypotheses, build solutions, and test stuff. Not only in the product, but taking care of the company's processes in a fractal way.
You must know how to execute and tangibilize stuff.
It is no use having in-depth research without exceptional execution. Likewise, there is no point in having excellent execution without in-depth research. The two pillars are complementary, and we have a different opinion on this issue regarding the market current status quo.
The product is only valuable when it's in prod and UX and UI are part of the same value delivery.
If one fails, everything breaks.

What we are looking for
We are looking for people passionate about design, with the desire to develop broadly within the area. Technology is the most important part of our business, so we need people who want to know more about our market, how the payment ecosystem works and help us to change it. We want people that connect with our business, and we want to build something that will change Brazil.

Minimum qualifications
Are passionate about design;
Can discuss abstract concepts and flows deeply;
Can materialize service flows through research input;
Can manage, help and teach inexperienced designers;
Understand that premade frameworks are only tools;
Understand how the front-end development works;
Have previous visual design experience (Typography, Contrast, and Color);
Have previous experience on interaction design;
Have previous experience on building low and high fidelity prototypes;
Have previous experience on responsive design (Desktop / Mobile);
Have previous experience on motion design (Easing, Timing, and Semantic Animation);
Have previous experience in developing scalable and consistent Design Systems;
Have previous experience with branding and marketing;
Have previous experience with team management;
Have previous experience with print design.
Preferred qualifications
Have previous experience with research and discovery processes (Upstream);
Have previous knowledge about HCI (Human-Computer Interaction);
Have previous experience in research, upstream / discovery flows;
Have previous experience on building something you are proud of;
Have side projects on track record.
