Be the impulse we want
Hi, we’re Linx Impulse! We are born as a business union of 4 top-grade companies, Neemu, Chaordic, Percycle and Shopback.
Our objective is to give a complete solution to online and offline stores, going along through the customer journey and generating memorable and customised experiences.
We are Big Data for real, terabytes of data passes through here per day. Also, we have petabytes of data stored and reach an average of 500,000 rpm (requisitions per minute) on our systems daily.
As a fullstack developer you will need to follow devops guidelines, a mix of development and operation. You will be in charge of developing and maintaining high-availability systems, keeping them up and reliable. You will be responsible for collecting a huge amount of data from both client side users like page views and orders information, and ecommerces catalog data, such as product catalog and availability. In order to build these beautiful systems we commonly use NodeJS, Python, GO and Scala as the main languages, but we are not limited to them, we expect you to contribute with some new knowledge to improve even more our services. Although most of our routine is based on backend development, some of our applications collect information from users on the client side, and for that kind of maintenance we expect you to be able to also bring front-end development and debugging skills, such as profiling, client side storage and performance.
Our development workflow is strongly based on automated tests, good distributed development practices and devops culture. We use Amazon (AWS) as a cloud provider for most of our infrastructure, so this kind of knowledge is a great plus!
If you are an experienced developer who likes to work with huge loads of data and interested not only on technologies that you already know, but to think out of the box, new challenges and go beyond development, with some action and operation, well... It is you who we are looking for!
